The Herald Crime Reporter A Kadoma man is believed to have been murdered before his body was placed across a railway line and ran over by a locomotive yesterday. Police discovered that the body had a deep cut on the head. National police spokesperson Assistant Commissioner Paul Nyathi confirmed the incident. “Police in Kadoma are investigating circumstances surrounding a case of suspected murder in which Takesure Samwari (21) is suspected to have been murdered before his body was placed across a railway line at the 440 km peg along Machipanda-Dabuka Railways, Mainline, Kadoma. “The body was ran over by a locomotive on January 20, 2023 and was found with a deep cut on the head. Anyone with information to report at any nearest Police Station,” he said. Police are also investigating and looking for a suspect, Tongai Ruzvezve (39) who struck his estranged wife and young sister with an axe at Muchemwa Village, Mamina, Mhodoro on January 19 at around 3pm. Meanwhile Police in Zvishavane are investigating circumstances surrounding a shooting incident in which a 27 year man was shot on the stomach by an unknown suspect, while walking along a strip road with a friend, from Kroomdrai, Mimosa area near Dadaya High School on January 20. The complainant is admitted at a local hospital in Zvishavane.